.TH "LEKTRA" "1" "" "\[em] User Commands"
.SH NAME
\f[B]lektra\f[R] \[em] is a high\-performance PDF reader that
prioritizes screen space and control.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP
.EX
lektra [OPTIONS] [FILE_PATH(s)...]
.EE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]lektra\f[R] is a fast, keyboard\-driven PDF viewer .
By default, it detaches from the terminal immediately after, so your
shell prompt returns right away.
Use \f[CR]\-\-foreground\f[R] to suppress this and keep lektra attached
to the terminal \[em] useful for debugging or capturing log output.
.PP
Supported file formats: PDF, XPS, OpenXPS, CBZ (Comic Book Zip),
FictionBook 2.0 (FBZ), EPUB, MOBI, PNG, JPEG, TIFF, SVG, DjVu (only if
compiled with djvu support)
.PP
Multiple files may be opened at once, optionally arranged in a
split\-view layout.
.PP
Command line options are described below:
.TP
\f[CR]FILE_PATH(s)\f[R]
One or more PDF files to open on startup.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-list\-commands\f[R]
Print a list of all available commands and exit.
.TP
\f[CR]\-p PAGE_NUMBER\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-page PAGE_NUMBER\f[R]
Jump to the given page number immediately after opening the file.
Defaults to \f[CR]\-1\f[R] (no override; reopen at last remembered
position).
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-layout LAYOUT\f[R]
Set the initial view layout.
Valid values:
.PP
.TS
tab(@);
l l.
T{
Value
T}@T{
Description
T}
_
T{
\f[CR]single\f[R]
T}@T{
One document pane
T}
T{
\f[CR]vertical\f[R]
T}@T{
Two panes side\-by\-side (default)
T}
T{
\f[CR]horizontal\f[R]
T}@T{
Two panes stacked top\-to\-bottom
T}
T{
