T}
.TE
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-vsplit\f[R]
Open the supplied file(s) in a \f[B]vertical\f[R] split view.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-hsplit\f[R]
Open the supplied file(s) in a \f[B]horizontal\f[R] split view.
.TP
\f[CR]\-s SESSION_NAME\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-session SESSION_NAME\f[R]
Load a named session on startup.
See \f[B]lektra\-config(5)\f[R] for how sessions are stored.
.TP
\f[CR]\-c CONFIG_PATH\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-config CONFIG_PATH\f[R]
Path to an alternative \f[CR]config.toml\f[R] file.
Overrides the default location.
See \f[B]lektra\-config(5)\f[R] for the full configuration reference.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-about\f[R]
Show the \f[I]About Lektra\f[R] dialog and exit.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-tutorial\f[R]
Open with the built\-in tutorial file loaded.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-foreground\f[R]
Do \f[B]not\f[R] detach from the terminal.
The process stays in the foreground, which is useful for capturing
stdout/stderr or running under a debugger.
.TP
\f[CR]\-\-synctex\-forward {pdf\-file}#{src\-file}:{line}:{col}\f[R]
Perform a SyncTeX forward search, jumping to the source location in the
PDF.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Only available when lektra is compiled with synctex support.\f[R]
.RE
.TP
\f[CR]\-h\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R]
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
\f[CR]\-v\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-version\f[R]
Print the version string and exit.
.SS STARTUP BEHAVIOUR
On launch, lektra performs a \f[B]double\-fork\f[R] so that the
grandchild process is fully detached from the calling TTY and the parent
shell returns immediately.
The re\-executed grandchild always receives the implicit
\f[CR]\-\-foreground\f[R] flag, so the detach logic runs exactly once.
.PP
Pass \f[CR]\-\-foreground\f[R] explicitly to skip the fork entirely
\[em] useful when running lektra from a compositor script, systemd user
unit, or test harness.
.SS FILES
.TP
\f[CR]$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/lektra/config.toml\f[R]
Default user configuration file.
See \f[B]lektra\-config(5)\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]$XDG_DATA_HOME/lektra/sessions/\f[R]
Directory where named sessions are persisted.
.SS EXAMPLES
Open a single file:
.IP
.EX
lektra document.pdf
.EE
.PP
Open at page 42:
.IP
.EX
lektra \-p 42 document.pdf
.EE
.PP
Open two files side\-by\-side:
.IP
.EX
lektra \-\-vsplit file1.pdf file2.pdf
.EE
.PP
Open with a custom config and a specific layout:
.IP
.EX
lektra \-\-config \[ti]/dotfiles/lektra.toml \-\-layout book thesis.pdf
.EE
.PP
Run in the foreground (e.g.\ to see log output):
.IP
.EX
lektra \-\-foreground document.pdf
.EE
.PP
Load a saved session:
.IP
.EX
lektra \-\-session research
.EE
